Using Python as Calculator 
The interpreter acts as a simple
 calculator: you can type an 
expression at it and 
it will write the value.
Expression syntax is straightforward: 
the operators are +, -, * and / work just like in most other languages (for example, Pascal or C); parentheses (())
 can be utilized for its grouping all together.
 The first thing that youâ€™ll need to do is to import the tkinter package. 
 The tkinter package can be used to create a Graphical User Interface (GUI) in Python.
The steps play important role in this.
